eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 40 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Prior treatment-related toxicity resolved to =< grade 1 or baseline with the exception of alopecia

b) Will be status post macroscopically complete resection of disease with one of the following poor risk features in surgical pathology specimen:
* Malignant involvement of 2 or more regional lymph nodes
* Extracapsular extension of nodal disease
* Microscopically involved mucosal margins of resection
* T3 or T4 pathologic stage (excluding T3N0 laryngeal squamous cell cancer)
* Perineural involvement
* Oral cavity or oropharyngeal primaries with nodal disease at levels IV or V
Bilirubin < 1.5 mg% with no evidence of obstructive liver disease
World Health Organization (WHO)-confirmed AML, other than acute promyelocytic leukemia (APL)
Pregnancy or lactation; patients must use effective contraception during the course of the clinical trial

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Toxicity data will be presented by severity for each dose group. The incidence of toxicity related dose reductions and treatment discontinuations will be summarized for each dose group. If there are a sufficient number of patients in each dose group, chi square analyses will be used to compare dose groups with respect to the incidence of specific toxicities.
outcome_measures.measure: Recommended phase II dose of vorinostat determined according to dose-limiting toxicities graded using Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events version 4.0 (CTCAE v4.0) (Phase I)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: TTF will be examined using Kaplan-Meier methods.
outcome_measures.measure: Time to treatment failure (TTF) (Expansion cohort only)
Percentage of Participants with CR, Determined by the IRC on the Basis of CT Scans Alone
outcome_measures.time_frame: Within 6 to 8 weeks after Day 1 of Cycle 6 (up to approximately 23 weeks) (1 cycle:21days)
